        <p>Following are the primary tasks that you can perform when using macros:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Record Macros </span> For most tasks that apply to the XML&#160;Editor, you can record macros to use in your <MadCap:variable name="Other.Product" /> files.<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.OnlineLive"> See <MadCap:xref href="../../../Macros/Recording_Macros.htm">Recording Macros</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText></li>
            <li><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Play Back Macros </span> You can use, or play back, macros you have recorded. This applies them to content in your <MadCap:variable name="Other.Product" /> files.<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.OnlineLive"> See <MadCap:xref href="../../../Macros/Playing_Back_Macros.htm">Playing Back Macros</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText></li>
            <li><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Manage Macros </span> You can rename macros and delete those that you no longer need. You can also assign shortcuts to macros.<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.OnlineLive"> See <MadCap:xref href="../../../Macros/Managing_Macros.htm">Managing Macros</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText></li>
        </ul>
    </body>
</html>